



To Doctor James Craik, of the Virginia Regiment.
[Alexandria, 16 December 1755]



So soon as the Vessel with the Stores and medicines arrives, you are to embrace the first opportunity that offers, of conveying
[218]
up your Chest, and proceeding, yourself, to Winchester.1 You are to provide yourself here, with what you think will be wanting for the Hospital, and bring them up with you; taking care to purchase no more than is absolutely necessary, for the support and relief of the Regiment. Given at Alexandria &c.

December 16th 1755.

